column1: source,"target","similarity","setnence_num_target","target_sent","source_sent"
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.516341231370773,44,"I tell you 'tis not very well!","Does 't not go well?"
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.516687089078465,38,"Faith, I have heard too much, and your words and performances are no kin together.","'Faith, that was not so well."

#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.520686245662714,18,"I think I can discover him, if you please To get good guard and go along with me.","That you shall surely find him, Lead to the Sagittary the raised search, And there will I be with him."

#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.555861334841759,33,"My money is almost spent, I have been tonight exceedingly well cudgeled, and I think the issue will be I shall have so much experience for my pains, and so, with no money at all and a little more wit, return again to Venice.","I have brought you from Venice."

#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.566665807163479,11,"But I beseech you, If 't be your pleasure and most wise consent -  As partly I find it is - that your fair daughter, At this odd-even and dull watch o' th' night, Transported with no worse nor better guard But with a knave of common hire, a gondolier, To the gross clasps of a lascivious Moor: If this be known to you, and your allowance, We then have done you bold and saucy wrongs.","Now, sir, be judge yourself Whether I in any just term am affined To love the Moor."
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.576688605531877,50,"Why, then, Othello and Desdemona return again to Venice.","Sir, there is especial commission come from Venice to depute Cassio in Othello's place."
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.590116191033066,48,"Ay, and said nothing but what I protest intendment of doing.","I protest, in the sincerity of love and honest kindness."
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.661678835369275,45,"I will make myself known to Desdemona.","First, I must tell thee this: Desdemona is directly in love with him."
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.701303143782179,57,"O, villain that I am!","I am a very villain else."
#Iago_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.71007235783041,19,"Signior, it is the Moor.","Now, sir, be judge yourself Whether I in any just term am affined To love the Moor."
#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.424867838397896,57,"O, villain that I am!","O, I have lost my reputation!"

#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.438568509121802,40,"The jewels you have had from me to deliver to Desdemona would half have corrupted a votaress.","My suit to her Is that she will to virtuous Desdemona Procure me some access."

#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.441040206533169,41,"You have told me she hath received them, and returned me expectations and comforts of sudden respect and acquaintance, but I find none.","She is persuaded I will marry her out of her own love and flattery, not out of my promise."

#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.459657142038673,35,"Every day thou daff'st me with some device, Iago, and rather, as it seems to me now, keep'st from me all conveniency than suppliest me with the least advantage of hope.","Yet I beseech you, If you think fit, or that it may be done, Give me advantage of some brief discourse With Desdemon alone."

#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.487445920702462,55,"I have no great devotion to the deed, And yet he hath given me satisfying reasons.","If my offense be of such mortal kind That nor my service past nor present sorrows Nor purposed merit in futurity Can ransom me into his love again, But to know so must be my benefit."

#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.501342839453646,50,"Why, then, Othello and Desdemona return again to Venice.","Great Jove, Othello guard, And swell his sail with thine own powerful breath, That he may bless this bay with his tall ship, Make love's quick pants in Desdemona's arms, Give renewed fire to our extincted spirits, And bring all Cyprus comfort!"
#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.501948758147148,38,"Faith, I have heard too much, and your words and performances are no kin together.","I' faith, sweet love, I was coming to your house."

#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.503052538504992,46,"If she will return me my jewels, I will give over my suit and repent my unlawful solicitation.","She is persuaded I will marry her out of her own love and flattery, not out of my promise."
#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.50469316876827,30,"But that was but courtesy.","'Tis my breeding That gives me this bold show of courtesy."
#Cassio_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.564265008688095,45,"I will make myself known to Desdemona.","My suit to her Is that she will to virtuous Desdemona Procure me some access."

#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.478328207009716,23,"I confess it is my shame to be so fond, but it is not in my virtue to amend it.","And till she come, as truly as to heaven I do confess the vices of my blood, So justly to your grave ears I'll present How I did thrive in this fair lady's love, And she in mine."
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.478374844924074,40,"The jewels you have had from me to deliver to Desdemona would half have corrupted a votaress.","I do not think but Desdemona's honest."

#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.501648636359941,41,"You have told me she hath received them, and returned me expectations and comforts of sudden respect and acquaintance, but I find none.","My story being done, She gave me for my pains a world of sighs."
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.536148544429727,20,"What will I do, think'st thou?","What if I do obey?"
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.545319990771168,42,""Very well." "Go to!" I cannot go to, man, nor 'tis not very well!","Go to, well said, well said."

#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.547937879315344,34,"I do not find That thou deal'st justly with me.","And when I told thee he was of my counsel In my whole course of wooing, thou cried'st "Indeed?" And didst contract and purse thy brow together As if thou then hadst shut up in thy brain Some horrible conceit."
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.567716758086985,28,"I cannot believe that in her.","My life upon her faith!"
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.586070687728892,50,"Why, then, Othello and Desdemona return again to Venice.","I took you for that cunning whore of Venice That married with Othello."
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.593503172964901,57,"O, villain that I am!","Villain, be sure thou prove my love a whore!"
#Othello_Oth,"#Roderigo_Oth",0.645125132559523,45,"I will make myself known to Desdemona.","These things to hear Would Desdemona seriously incline."
